# Security, Cost, And Side Effects

Do not commit secrets, API keys, tokens, private credentials, or real customer data.

Prefer `.env.example` for required variables. Real secrets stay in local `.env`, Supabase, DigitalOcean, GSM, Infisical/OpenBao, or other approved secret stores.

All external side effects must be governed through LinkSkills capability leases in the MVO design, even if the implementation is simplified.

Risky side effects include:

- sending emails
- publishing public sites
- writing to CRM
- creating invoices
- charging payments
- modifying production workflows
- deploying infrastructure

For MVO, outreach email is draft-only unless explicitly approved.

Cost controls are first-class. Agents must avoid unnecessary premium model usage and record any long-running or expensive operation.

Do not introduce major new dependencies, services, or paid tools without recording the decision.
